          "id": "w-mo8a0my5-9bc50c856a74",
          "type": "brief",
          "phase": "open",
          "title": "Oculus: Spider page cos issues",
          "body": "Cost aggregation pulls cross-plugin data through Stacks\nD10 recommends direct book reads from spider into animator/sessions. This is already the pattern (see spider/oculus-routes.ts:64 for transcripts), but it does couple Spider to Animator's on-disk schema in more places. If the Animator ever renames or restructures the sessions book, Spider breaks in more places than it does today. An AnimatorApi method (sumCostForSessions(ids: string[]): { costUsd, inputTokens, outputTokens }) would be a cleaner boundary if this coupling becomes problematic. Not worth the abstraction for this commission alone, but a candidate for a future \"decouple spider from animator stacks\" cleanup if more places grow this dependency.\n\nThe brief's token format uses no .toLocaleString() precedent\nThe brief's example 12,222 input, 12,223 output implies a , thousands separator (en-US locale). Users viewing the dashboard in a non-US locale will see their system's grouping separator if we use Number.toLocaleString() without a locale argument (e.g. 12.222 in German locales). To match the brief exactly for all viewers, the implementation should pass 'en-US' explicitly (n.toLocaleString('en-US')). This is a small formatter-implementation detail the spec writer should name explicitly.",
          "codex": "nexus",
          "createdAt": "2026-04-21T07:02:21.485Z",
          "updatedAt": "2026-04-21T07:02:21.485Z"
        }
      },
      "startedAt": "2026-04-21T07:02:23.464Z",
