        "output": "All four artifacts are now written to plan `w-mo8a0my5-9bc50c856a74`:\n\n**Inventory** — Brief context, scope & blast radius across animator/spider, prior commission summary, key-file walkthrough (rig-view.ts, animator types.ts, animator.ts, the two test suites), the five other Spider→animator/sessions read sites, the three other cross-plugin readBook callers, current state of observation #2 (already satisfied), adjacent patterns (cross-apparatus read convention, AnimatorApi shape, bulk-query patterns, graceful-missing-session semantics), existing context, and doc/code discrepancies.\n\n**Scope** (2 items):\n- **S1** — Introduce new read-side bulk cost/token method on AnimatorApi + migrate `enrichRigView` / `enrichRigViews` to use it.\n- **S2** — Ensure Spider's token-count formatter passes `'en-US'` explicitly.\n\n**Decisions** (6, with 3 surfacing to the patron):\n- **D1** (surface) — Method shape: brief's aggregate-only suggestion vs per-session map. Recommendation: aggregate-only (per brief); surfaced because aggregate-only cannot cover the per-engine breakdown the existing rig-view needs.\n- **D2** (pre-filled) — Method lives on AnimatorApi.\n- **D3** (surface) — Decouple only rig-view.ts or all six Spider→animator/sessions read sites? Recommendation: narrow (rig-view only).\n- **D4** (pre-filled) — Proceed despite prior author's \"not worth it\" hedge.\n- **D5** (surface) — S2 disposition given code already satisfies it. Recommendation: exclude (already done).\n- **D6** (pre-filled) — Silent-skip for missing sessions (preserves existing enrichRigView semantics).\n\n**Observations** — Architectural tension with parlour.md's cross-apparatus-read convention (needs a tie-break rule), N-round-trip in rig-view worth collapsing via `find({where:['id','IN',ids]})`, three architecture docs that will lag, cross-dashboard token-formatting drift (Parlour/Astrolabe), wider Spider-read surface, error-policy naming for the new method, test-brittleness caveat for rig-view.test.ts, and the unused-RigView-fields watch item."
      },
